course.subject: MATH
course.name: Independent Study: Advanced Technologies for Fine Grained Entity Typing
course.description: This course will study the fine grained entity typing. Student will use programming tools and machine learning models to conduct the research. The student is expected to learn the knowledge in NLP and gain research experience. The student will meet the instructor at least once a week to present the materials and discuss with the instructor on the materials. The student should seek the course instructor's approval to take this course.
